  31. (* Registers available for register allocation *)

  33. (* Integer register map:
  34.     0                   temporary, null register for some operations (volatile)
  35.     1                   temporary (volatile)
  36.     2 - 5               function arguments and results (volatile)
  37.     6                   function arguments and results (preserved by C)
  38.     7 - 9               general purpose, preserved by C
  39.     10                  domain state pointer (preserved by C)
  40.     11                  allocation pointer (preserved by C)
  41.     12                  general purpose  (preserved by C)
  42.     13                  trap pointer (preserved by C)
  43.     14                  return address (volatile)
  44.     15                  stack pointer (preserved by C)
  45.   Floating-point register map:
  46.     0, 2, 4, 6          function arguments and results (volatile)
  47.     1, 3, 5, 7          general purpose (volatile)
  48.     8 - 14              general purpose, preserved by C
  49.     15                  temporary, preserved by C

  51. Note: integer register r12 is used as GOT pointer by some C compilers.
  52. The code generated by OCaml does not need a GOT pointer, using PC-relative
  53. addressing instead for accessing the GOT.  This frees r12 as a
  54. general-purpose register. *)

  98. (* Calling conventions *)

  100. ‌let size_domainstate_args = 64 * size_int

  102. ‌let calling_conventions
  103.     first_int last_int first_float last_float make_stack stack_ofs arg =
  104.   let loc = Array.make (Array.length arg) Reg.dummy in
  105.   let int = ref first_int in
  106.   let float = ref first_float in
  107.   let ofs = ref stack_ofs in
  108.   for i = 0 to Array.length arg - 1 do
  109.     match arg.(i) with
  110.     | Val | Int | Addr as ty ->
  111.         if !int <= last_int then begin
  112.           loc.(i) <- phys_reg !int;
  113.           incr int
  114.         end else begin
  115.           loc.(i) <- stack_slot (make_stack !ofs) ty;
  116.           ofs := !ofs + size_int
  117.         end
  118.     | Float ->
  119.         if !float <= last_float then begin
  120.           loc.(i) <- phys_reg !float;
  121.           incr float
  122.         end else begin
  123.           loc.(i) <- stack_slot (make_stack !ofs) Float;
  124.           ofs := !ofs + size_float
  125.         end
  126.   done;
  127.   (loc, Misc.align (max 0 !ofs) 16) (* Keep stack 16-aligned. *)

  129. ‌let incoming ofs =
  130.   if ofs >= 0
  131.   then Incoming ofs
  132.   else Domainstate (ofs + size_domainstate_args)
  133. ‌let outgoing ofs =
  134.   if ofs >= 0
